x4freetext: 6-MeV electrostatic accelerator
Proton recoil spectrometer based on a stilbene
crystal (40x40 mm) was used.
The relative uncertainties of the neutron spectra
took into account:
uncertainty of calibration of the energy
scale
uncertainty of the stability of the electronic
equipment
uncertainty of the value of the light
output
uncertainty of the spectrometer efficiency
uncertainty of the solid angle of the
stilbene crystal
Entry was approved by Dr. D.E.Gremyachkin.
Lithium targets were prepared by evaporation LiF onto
0.5-mm copper backings.
statistical error, no more than 5%

x4freetext: Deuterium targets were deuterium absorbed in ~ 1 mg/cm2
thick Ti layer deposited on 0.5-mm copper backings.
The correction was introduced for the transmission
function of the lead filter which was calculated using
the Monte Carlo method. Uncertainties were 1-2 % in the
considered energy range.
statistical error, no more than 5%
